# pytest E2E Conventions

## Markers

Every test must have at least one `@pytest.mark.<fr_id>` marker linking it to an SRS requirement (FR-1 through FR-25). Non-functional tests use `nfr_perf` or `nfr_compat`.

```python
@pytest.mark.fr5
class TestDiscoveryDisplay:
    def test_shows_four_pokemon(self, clean_page):
        """FR-5: Ranking screen displays exactly 4 Pokemon cards."""
```

## Test Structure

- Class-based grouping: one test class per logical feature area
- Docstrings on every test method referencing the SRS requirement ID
- Use fixtures from `conftest.py` (`clean_page`, `seeded_page`, etc.)

## Fixtures

- `clean_page` -- fresh browser page with cleared LocalStorage
- `seeded_page` -- page with pre-seeded LocalStorage (Gen 1 completed)
- `all_gens_completed_page` -- page with all 9 generations completed
- `base_url` -- the app URL (session-scoped)

## File Naming

- `test_home_page.py` -- FR-1 to FR-4
- `test_phase_a.py` -- FR-5 to FR-10
- `test_phase_b.py` -- FR-11 to FR-16
- `test_championship.py` -- FR-17 to FR-21
- `test_persistence.py` -- FR-22 to FR-25
- `test_performance.py` -- NFR performance
- `test_responsive.py` -- NFR compatibility
